  <front>
   <head>Song II</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="sestet">
     <l n="1" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">Thyrsis, when we parted, swore</l>
     <l n="2" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">Ere the spring he would return.</l>
     <l n="3" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">Ah, what means yon violet flower,</l>
     <l n="4" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">And the buds that deck the thorn?</l>
     <l n="5" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">'Twas the lark that upward sprung!</l>
     <l n="6" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">'Twas the nightingale that sung!</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="sestet">
     <l n="7" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">Idle notes, untimely green,</l>
     <l n="8" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">Why such unavailing haste?</l>
     <l n="9" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">Western gales and skies serene</l>
     <l n="10" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">Prove not always winter past.</l>
     <l n="11" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">Cease my doubts, my fears to move;</l>
     <l n="12" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">Spare the honour of my love.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
